OL,3,CMan who murdered and dismembered
OL,4,Clodger has sentence increased
OL,6,FHe continued: "It was Atkins who had
OL,7,Fcommitted the murder, it was Atkins
OL,8,Fwho dismembered the body, it was
OL,9,FAtkins who took parts of the body away
OL,10,Ffrom the flat and concealed them."
OL,12,FRuling that both sentences were unduly
OL,13,Flenient, Lord Justice Bean said: "We
OL,14,Fare very conscious of the fact that
OL,15,Fthe learned judge had heard all the
OL,16,Fevidence and great respect is to be
OL,17,Faccorded to the evaluation of the
OL,18,Ffacts by the judge who has presided
OL,19,Fover the trial.
